Casting Call (Non-Union) for COUPLES/POLYCULES - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of clients in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions include some scripted elements to prepare, and then some improv with prompts.

We are currently interested in filming with mature couples, queer couples, interracial couples, or throuples/polycules of various gender identity combinations. All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. 

All experience levels with acting are welcome, including experienced actors with less experienced partners. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are October 10 through 17, but more will occur in the future so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $90 CAD per performer, wit the expectation of some prepared material, duration: 1 hour

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

Geplant sind kurze POV-Sketche, Beziehungsszenen, Alltagssatire und emotionale Mini-Dramen ‚Äì alles mit einem Augenzwinkern und klarer Rollenstruktur.

Drehort ist Berlin.

Was ich suche:

- Schauspielerin im Alter von 28 bis 44 Jahren  

- Spa√ü an geskripteten Szenen und klaren Rollenbildern  

- Offen f√ºr verschiedene Rollen (z. B. Freundin, Kollegin, Date, Aff√§re, Nachbarin etc.)  

- Gef√ºhl f√ºr Timing, Mimik und Punchlines  

- Keine Angst vor Kamera, Humor oder Drama

Was dich erwartet:

- Kreative Zusammenarbeit mit einem Creator, der Storytelling & Timing liebt  

- Szenen mit klarer Struktur, aber Raum f√ºr eigene Ideen  

- M√∂glichkeit, dich als wiederkehrende Figur zu etablieren  

- Hinweis zur Verg√ºtung: Das Projekt befindet sich aktuell in der Aufbauphase und wird zun√§chst ohne feste Bezahlung umgesetzt. Ziel ist es, gemeinsam etwas Starkes aufzubauen ‚Äì mit Credits in jedem Clip und der Option auf langfristige Zusammenarbeit, sobald das Projekt w√§chst.

Interesse?  

Dann schreib mir direkt hier oder per Mail an Dennis.Laubert@Web.de.

Gerne mit kurzem Video, Link zu deinem Profil oder einfach ein paar Zeilen zu dir.

Liebe Gr√º√üe, 

Dennis Laubert

items.text:
TENNESSEE WILLIAMS MONOLOGUES | LISTENING SESSION

Online | Free

Hi Everyone,

On **Monday evening October 13, 7-8:30pm Eastern**, I'll present this free online session. This is a series of mostly-Tennessee Williams based free class sessions, at the end of which we will also talk about the upcoming January Clarksdale Workshops: Acting and Playwriting sessions in Tennessee Williams' Mississippi Delta (Jan 4-10), taught by me and playwright Lucy Thurber and director Jenna Worsham.

On Monday we'll listen to 8-9 monologues I'll select from Tennessee Williams characters that are less known than his most famous ones. It's amazing to hear the variety in his writing. This is part of a project I'm working on that I'll tell you more about that night. When you reserve, let me know if you want to read. It's also fine to just come and listen.

Join us!

**TO RESERVE:** email **classes@monologueaudition.com**

*****can't do this one? email classes@monologueaudition.com to hear about the next ones*****

Karen

**KAREN KOHLHAAS** is an Atlantic Theater Company founding member, director, and senior teacher. She is a master teacher of Practical Aesthetic acting technique, and teaches acting, directing, monologues and cold reading, online, in New York City, in Clarksdale, Mississippi and around the US. She is a Tennessee Williams scholar and curator of the Tennessee Williams Rectory Museum, and is editing a documentary series about Williams' time in the Mississippi Delta. The Clarksdale Workshops are residentail week-long trainings for actors and playwrights (Williams scene study and playwriting in January), and for actors and teachers (Monologue Audition training in August). For more information on classes please visit art-and-audition.com, and TennWmsDelta.com.

Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

PROFESSIONAL HEADSHOT PROMOTION

We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals ‚Äì17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer ¬£700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

CASTING CALL 

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production 

Project Type: UCF BFA Short Film 

Union Status: Non-Union 

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected 

Shooting Dates: TBD 

Shooting Location: Orlando area 

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her. 

This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production. 

Character Breakdowns: 

MONOMAY: Female, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants. 

JASON: Male, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma. 

FAN CLUB: Any gender, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention. 

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

OR

Fill out this Google form: 
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeN2krq62Mec2KpTeJrleyIirLMgRBfIJkdh2N6B6q_VwMk3Q/viewform?usp=dialog

items.text:
CHRISTMAS CASTING CALL ‚Äì ENSEMBLE CAST and GROTTO ELVES

 

Seeking talented performers for this year‚Äôs production of The Magical Christmas Adventure ‚Äî a multi-award-winning live performance and immersive attraction based near Newbury, Berkshire. The production combines the best of pantomime with interactive entertainment, inviting audiences to become part of the story.

With an all-new show for 2025, we are casting for principal roles to join our cast. Each tour runs for approximately 2 hours, with groups departing every 10 minutes ‚Äî up to 48 tours per day.

 

Salary:

¬£15.00 hourly rate

Accommodation will be included

Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner are all provided for you.

 

Location: Headley, Berkshire

Dates:

Rehearsal from 18th November

Soft Launch 22th November

1st full performance day 23rd December

Last performance day 24th December

Approx 22 days in total

 

ROLES:

 

GRAND MASTER TOY MAKER

Santa's most trusted elf and the head of toy production at the North Pole.

 

SNOWFLAKE

In charge of keeping all the snowballs at the Ice Castle ready for battle whenever needed.

 

SPARKLE

A friendly, bubbly, energetic, and knowledgeable elf who welcomes guests to the North Pole.

 

GROTTO ELF

You'll be a bubbly, charismatic personality meeting families to take them to and stay with them doing their meeting with Santa.

 

If you would like to join us on this magical adventure, please email your CV, headshot and covering letter to [mike@themagicalchristmasadventure.co.uk](mailto:mike@themagicalchristmasadventure.co.uk)

 

[www.themagicalchristmasadventure.co.uk](http://www.themagicalchristmasadventure.co.uk)

**RE:SCULPT ‚Äì Instructor Auditions | London**

** **

**Think you‚Äôve got the fire to lead from the front?**

We‚Äôre on the hunt for instructors who bring serious energy, bold vibes, and unstoppable presence to every RE:SCULPT class. This is your chance to join a brand that‚Äôs shaking up the fitness industry and setting new standards for what a reformer-inspired strength workout can be.

At RE:SCULPT, we don‚Äôt just teach classes - we *create experiences.* You‚Äôll need to lift the room, command the energy, and connect with clients through every beat and every move. You‚Äôll coach with precision, motivate with purpose, and deliver a workout that keeps clients coming back for more.

 

We‚Äôre looking for instructors who:
* Have undeniable stage presence and confidence on the mic.
* Understand how to blend performance with purpose - ensuring every workout has a vibe and is technically strong.
* Can create awesome energy while maintaining control and flow with the beat of the music.
* Can embrace the RE:SCULPT brand, values and community.

N**on-union LatinX** female lead for our next vertical drama.

Project - When Time Brings Us Together

Director - Sid Zanforlin

Dates - Oct 21st- Oct 29th (7 days in that time frame)

Rate - $350/day

Production Company - Ottawood Film

Location - Richmond Hill

Flights and accommodations will be covered for actors travelling from outside Toronto.

**Storyline**

Kindhearted and beautiful factory worker Diane Brooker enters a marriage of convenience with powerful CEO Steve Fulcher, only to be separated by tragedy and memory loss. A year later, fate brings them back together. Sparking a journey of rediscovery, romance, and Diane‚Äôs transformation from a humiliated outcast to a confident woman who reclaims her dignity and love.

**Diane Gomez 45-years-old**

A single LatinX mom that would do anything for her 20ish son. When younger she was a dancer and could charm anyone but has recently lost her confidence.

Please submit a head shot and resume to ottawoodcasting@gmail.com

Jigsaw Casting is looking for a George Washington lookalike in their mid 60‚Äôs for a Software Campaign across North America! 

We‚Äôre looking for MEN mid 60‚Äôs+ who bear an uncanny resemblance to George Washington. Have you ever been mistaken for the first president of the United States? Do you think you might be mistaken for good old G.W. if someone put the right kind of wig on you? If yes, this is for you!

No acting experience required, just a willingness to play along.

This shoots in Toronto, Canada if someone lives far from this location, travel and accommodation will be provided. 

IF YOU KNOW OF SOMEONE, PLEASE PASS THIS ON!

Compensation if selected: $6,675.00. CAD. Buyout is based on survival of the edit and includes all lifts, edits, versions. This is a non union job.

Must be available for these Important dates:

Recall: Saturday Oct 18th - 21st Via Zoom if you live far. In person if you are in Toronto.
Travel Days (for those who do not live in Toronto and has to fly in): Travel to Toronto Oct 27, Travel Home Oct 31 TBD
Wardrobe: Oct 27 and or 28th TBD (in Toronto)
Shoot Date: Oct 29 or Oct 30 - TBD Which day needed (in Toronto)

DEADLINE TO SUBMIT: ASAP OR BEFORE FRIDAY OCTOBER 17, 2025 AT 6PM. EST.

Submission Link: https://aircastle.ca/submit/g-dub

**Company:** LAS Bespoke ‚Äì Premium Automotive Detailing & Protection (Surrey, BC)
**Contact:** luxuryautospa.van@gmail.com
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Shoot Location:** Surrey, BC
**Shoot Date:** Flexible between October 14‚Äì18 (Exact day confirmed with actor)
**Time Commitment:** 2‚Äì3 hours
**Pay Rate:** $100 flat

**Project Description:**
We‚Äôre filming a short advertisement video for LAS Bespoke, a premium automotive brand known for ceramic coatings and paint protection. The video will feature you wearing our branded merch and delivering short, confident lines on camera. The ad will be used for social media and digital marketing.

**Character Breakdown:**
‚Ä¢ **Male (Caucasian)**
‚Ä¢ **Age:** 35‚Äì45
‚Ä¢ **Look:** Clean-cut, friendly, confident, and trustworthy appearance
‚Ä¢ **Personality:** Comfortable speaking naturally to camera, clear voice, good posture, and strong presence
‚Ä¢ **Experience:** Previous on-camera or commercial experience preferred but not required

**Requirements:**
‚Ä¢ Must be comfortable being filmed and following short scripts
‚Ä¢ Must be reliable, punctual, and presentable
‚Ä¢ Will be provided branded clothing for the shoot

**To Apply:**
Email **luxuryautospa.van@gmail.com** with the subject line **‚ÄúAd Casting ‚Äì Vancouver‚Äù** and include:
‚Ä¢ 2‚Äì3 recent photos or headshots
‚Ä¢ A short intro video or link to any previous work (if available)
‚Ä¢ Your availability between **October 14‚Äì18**

We‚Äôll contact selected candidates directly to confirm date and time.

items.text:
Actors (non-union) needed for a documentary regarding Elizabeth Johnson Jr who was the last convicted witch to be exonerated from the 1692 Salem Witchcraft Trials.

The ideal actor for Elizabeth will have strawberry blond or slight red hair, be of average height and able to portray early 20s.

Two additional actors will be needed as elders (40-60) who arrest her and walk her away.

The shoot will require one day in early November or early December on north of Boston. Pay will be negotiated.  Access to a late 17th century costume is a plus. Send headshot, resume and November, December availability to SalemHistoricalTours@gmail.com

*FUNDET! 

Jeg s√∏ger en hundeejer med en s√∏d familiehund (golden retriever, labrador, den slags, gerne i en lys farve) der kunne have lyst til at have deres hund med i nogle reklamebilleder/film der fremh√¶ver sommerhushygge i Blokhus üòäü¶Æüì∑ 

Vi laver nemlig nogle optagelser i Blokhus mandag-onsdag, hvor vi gerne vil have nogle scener med en hund. Det drejer sig om et par timer, gerne tirsdag eftermiddag, men andre tidspunkter er ogs√• mulige, og det er kun hunden der skal v√¶re med. Hunden skal agere sammen med en skuespilsfamilie. 
**Vi har 1500kr til betaling for dette.**

Skriv gerne en kommentar, send mig en besked eller mail p√• daniel@24copenhagen.dk, hvis du er interesseret.

God s√∏ndag!

CASTING CALL FOR A CSULB SENIOR FILM - UNPAID ROLE(S)

Looking for an Actor to play: **ABUELA**,** (Latina, 50‚Äì75)**

**----Other Roles** are still being casted as well, and can be found on our backstage listing and Instagram (@alma.short.film)

**Once a gifted singer, Abuela buried her passion for music after an early pregnancy forced her into a traditional life. Though she now discourages dreams she couldn‚Äôt fulfill, Alma‚Äôs love for music stirs old memories‚Äîand a quiet longing she thought she‚Äôd left behind.**

**Spanish required. Singing ability preferred.**

**Ethnicity: Latino / Hispanic**

**Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Video Reel, Resume**

**Required Skills:**
* **Languages: Spanish**

**Pre-Screen Requests: Video submission of Monologue and Reel **

**Once a gifted singer, Abuela buried her passion for music after an early pregnancy forced her into a traditional life. Though she now discourages dreams she couldn‚Äôt fulfill, Alma‚Äôs love for music stirs old memories‚Äîand a quiet longing she thought she‚Äôd left behind.**

**Spanish required. Singing ability preferred.**

**Ethnicity: Latino / Hispanic**

**Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Video Reel, Resume**

**Required Skills:**
* **Languages: Spanish**

**Pre-Screen Requests: Video submission of Monologue and Reel **

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì LONDON (November‚ÄìDecember)**

Hi Everyone,

I‚Äôm Ben, a founder trying to do something a bit mad in the run-up to Christmas.

I‚Äôve made a new family game and have **5,000 boxes to sell before Christmas**‚Ä¶ or I have to be a normal adult and go back to being an accountant again! 

We‚Äôre filming the real journey: street pitches, rejections, laughs, and small wins, all turned into short daily LinkedIn episodes (1‚Äì3 minutes each). Think *founder documentary meets chaos comedy*.

I‚Äôm looking for a few actors to jump in and help out, people who can play along naturally as friends, supporters, or street crew in different moments of the campaign.

**Location:** London

**When:** November‚ÄìDecember (run-up to Christmas)

**Paid freelance role:** Not a massive budget, but there is a budget.

**Commitment:** Half a day, 1 day a week for 4 weeks. Need 5 actors, one for each day of the week.

**Who suits this:**
* Chatty, funny, naturally comfortable on camera
* Up for improvising and rolling with the madness
* Down-to-earth, good energy, friendly vibe

If you‚Äôre **fun, talented, and up for helping make a tabletop game go viral**, drop me a DM with a short intro or clip.

Ben

items.text:
TENNESSEE WILLIAMS MONOLOGUES | LISTENING SESSION

Online | Free

Hi Everyone,

On **Monday evening October 13, 7-8:30pm Eastern**, I'll present this free online session. This is a series of mostly-Tennessee Williams based free class sessions, at the end of which we will also talk about the upcoming January Clarksdale Workshops: Acting and Playwriting sessions in Tennessee Williams' Mississippi Delta (Jan 4-10), taught by me and playwright Lucy Thurber and director Jenna Worsham.

On Monday we'll listen to 8-9 monologues I'll select from Tennessee Williams characters that are less known than his most famous ones. It's amazing to hear the variety in his writing. This is part of a project I'm working on that I'll tell you more about that night. When you reserve, let me know if you want to read. It's also fine to just come and listen.

Join us!

**TO RESERVE:** email **classes@monologueaudition.com**

*****can't do this one? email classes@monologueaudition.com to hear about the next ones*****

Karen

**KAREN KOHLHAAS** is an Atlantic Theater Company founding member, director, and senior teacher. She is a master teacher of Practical Aesthetic acting technique, and teaches acting, directing, monologues and cold reading, online, in New York City, in Clarksdale, Mississippi and around the US. She is a Tennessee Williams scholar and curator of the Tennessee Williams Rectory Museum, and is editing a documentary series about Williams' time in the Mississippi Delta. The Clarksdale Workshops are residentail week-long trainings for actors and playwrights (Williams scene study and playwriting in January), and for actors and teachers (Monologue Audition training in August). For more information on classes please visit art-and-audition.com, and TennWmsDelta.com.

items.text:
**SHORT FILM CREW CALL -***** Beyond the Blue Light***

*ISO of lgbtq, bipoc, and immigrant filmmakers to fill the following positions. All details below. Students welcome!*

*PAID:*

Studio Teacher (one minor 8 or 9 years old)

*IMDB Credit, Copy, Meals, Gas Stipend:*

2nd AC

Key Grip 

G&E Swing

Costumer (+ materials stipend)

Boom OP

PA

**Synopsis:**

*Beyond the Blue Light* is an emotionally charged drama about the cost of apathy in the chronically online era told through the perspective of two trans latine immigrants. 

**Location:**

Los Angeles: Hollywood & North Hollywood

**Dates:**

11/1 - 11/4

**About the Director:**

Simone Brazzini is an award winning filmmaker from Lima, Peru and now based in Los Angeles. Their debut LA short will be making its world premiere at the Micheaux Film Festival. They were recently named in a Deadline article and is a Soho House x Creative Futures Mentee. Simone founded Vibes Video in 2021, a production company that creates radically authentic work across all genres with a focus on lgbtq, bipoc, and neurodiverse voices on and off camera. 

**To Submit:**

Please email a portfolio and/or resume to vibesvideoproductions@gmail.com AND CC productions.fakeid@gmail.com

**THANK YOU**

WOMEN ARE 27% LESS LIKELY TO SURVIVE A CARDIAC ARREST COMPARED TO MEN!! 

Studies show women are less likely to survive cardiac arrest than men, primarily because they are less likely to receive bystander CPR.

Reasons for this include the public's fear of touching a woman's chest!! 

Learning how to save someone's live with a fully certificated and accredited course can take just 3 hours, learn how to do CPR, use and AED and how to be the person to save some grandmother, mother, daughter or aunty, be there reason someone else makes it home alive! 

Find out more about our courses by heading over to our website www.pegasusambulance.co.uk

My name is Luke Kenyon, and I‚Äôm a film student at SAE Liverpool. We‚Äôre currently working on a new short film project titled Last Night and are looking to cast two male-identifying actors (mid twenties)to join our team. This project is Non paid but we will be providing travel expenses as well as catering 

Shooting dates 9th - 15th November 2025 Liverpool, England

Synopsis -

On the anniversary of his best friend‚Äôs suicide, Aaron plans to end his own life. He ignores his mothers phone calls and edges closer towards his own end, until he unexpectedly hears a knock at his apartment front door. His best friend, Ben, appears in an attempt to make amends and guide Aaron away from darkness. This intimate drama, through one final, raw conversation, forces Aaron to choose between following the same path that Ben took a year ago, or answering the call that could save him.

Aaron:

Aaron, mid 20's, slightly introverted and reserved. A complicated character with a lot going on in his mind. His low confidence makes it hard for him to open up to others about his feelings, especially about the loss of his best friend (Ben), who meant the world to him. He loves music and even used to play in a band with Ben. 

Ben:

Ben, mid 20's, soft and sensitive personality. His battles with his own mental health has led him to an unfortunate end, which ultimately, has hurt someone very close to him (Aaron), although this was never his intention. Ben‚Äôs aim is to make some sort of amends from his past actions and to help Aaron not make the same mistake that he did. 

If you have any questions about the project or roles, please don‚Äôt hesitate to get in touch ‚Äî I‚Äôm happy to provide more information.

If you  are interested in applying, please use one of the provided links below or alternatively email me at 120206uk@saeinstitute.edu with your details, previous work, or portfolio. (Including heat shots) please provide which role you are applying for 

Thank you very much for your time We look forward to hearing from you!

Kind regards,

Luke Kenyon

Film Student, SAE Institute

https://www.backstage.com/casting/last-night-student-film-3019197/

https://www.starnow.com/casting/last-night-3021254/

https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3021242/last-night/

Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Sir Percy Shorter - chairman of the BMA, quite upper class and not too tall (Mid 40s+

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall

Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 

Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.

Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 

The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

¬£100 per day, plus IMDb credit, and also well fed on set. 

Experience required AND own transport is a MUST. 

To Apply: INBOX your details to us, your location, if you have OWN transport and relevant experience.

items.text:
I am seeking strong, versatile actors for key supporting roles in my upcoming feature film *EXHIT* ‚Äî a dark, character-driven psychological thriller set in Manchester. The film explores fate, control, and the descent into chaos after one man‚Äôs decision to hire a hitman to end his own life goes catastrophically wrong.

**ROLES**

**Urban Thug #1 ‚Äì ‚ÄúRico‚Äù (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)**
Charismatic and unpredictable. Energetic, naturalistic performer comfortable with improvisation and physicality. Any UK base.
*Required: 3rd‚Äì9th November.*

**Urban Thug #2 ‚Äì ‚ÄúDez‚Äù (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)**
Lean, intense, quick-thinking. Brings raw energy and realism; great at reacting in tense, improvised scenes. Any UK base.
*Required: 3rd‚Äì9th November.*

**Aisha (Female, 20s‚Äì30s)**
Jake‚Äôs nurse. Compassionate yet assertive. South Asian or mixed heritage preferred. Strong emotional range and natural chemistry with the lead.
*Required: 3rd‚Äì9th November.*
items.title:
STAY TUNE GUYS‚Ä¶.!

Rahat Shah,
A talented Fitness Model/Actor/Photographer and British Champion in Men‚Äôs Physique from Birmingham, UK! 

Hailing from a renowned art family in Pakistan‚Äôs film industry, Rahat‚Äôs creative genes are undeniable. With a string of achievements, including winning the British Champion award and Asians Beauty Pageant, Rahat has made a name for himself.

His upcoming Indian thriller film ‚ÄúSecond Chance‚Äù Directed by Sachin Karande is set to release soon, promising to captivate audiences worldwide.

As a cover model for numerous magazines, Rahat‚Äôs charm and physique have won hearts. Through his journey, he aims to inspire others, proving that hard work and dedication can lead to success. Stay tuned for an exciting story of passion, talent, and triumph!

Title: Stars Above Us

Shoot Dates: June 5‚Äì7, 2026

Location: Bowling Green, KY

We‚Äôre seeking passionate and reliable crew members for Stars Above Us, a student drama short film exploring friendship, loss, and mental health. This is a volunteer project‚Äîperfect for those looking to gain narrative experience, build credits, and expand reels in a collaborative, professional set environment. All production gear will be provided.

MY MOMMA‚ÄôS ERA: THE MUSICAL ‚Äì SEEN THROUGH MY MOTHER‚ÄôS LENS

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater ‚Äì 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(It‚Äôs recommended ‚Äî not required ‚Äî for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzeville‚Äôs rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago ‚Äî told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicago‚Äôs own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment ‚Äî it‚Äôs edutainment.

We're going live to raise funds for Dream Real Theatre Company, and your support is needed to bring productions to life to fund community outreach and mentorship programs and build our future performing media arts training facility.
Your support tonight helps us:

Fund production costs for the show (venue, lighting, costumes, sound, and more)

Launch our Mentors in the Streets program to reach youth through the arts

Build the BSW Performing Arts & Media Center, a home for community creativity and opportunity.

Actors wanted for Dick Whittington, Valley Theatre‚Äôs annual seasonal panto.

Audition date and time; 7.15pm, Monday 13th October 2025, at Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Performance dates: Sat 17th Jan 2026(afternoon and eve) and Sun 18th Jan 2026 (afternoon only);

Rehearsal days; Monday 7pm whole cast usually; Thursday eve selected scenes.

Valley Theatre‚Äôs traditional panto has become legendary in the area. As a community theatre we pride ourselves on keeping the prices family friendly without compromising on the quality. We like to offer a traditional storyline with well-loved panto routines, popular music, up-to-date and local references, strong on humour.

This is a great opportunity for actors wanting to gain unbeatable stage experience with a friendly and supportive production team.

Wide range of parts available for the experienced and beginner alike. No prep needed for the audition.

Please note: this is non-paying.

More details info@valleytheatre.co.uk

**Casting Call UBC Student Film "Sick Days"**

**Non Union, Unpaid, IMDB Credit. **

  Sick Days follows an adventurous, immigrant child who dares to indulge in his fascination of the outdoors despite his own fragile immune system, and his protective single mother's wishes to shield him from the nasty parts of the world ‚Äî both micro and macroscopic.

**Simon- Lead**

6 to 10, Male, Korean. Bilingual preferred

A timid and optimistic child quick to follow rules but ever curious to break them.

**Holly- Lead**

30s, female, korean. Fluent in Korean

A paranoid yet tender helicopter parent, shielding her son from the world.

**Anthony- Supporting**

6 to 10, Fun loving, extroverted kid, searching for camaraderie in a lonely new city.

Submit a Headshot and any supporting materials (demo-reel or self-tapes) to sickdays.film@gmail.com

Specific Shoot dates are tentative, but will either be December 6-8, or 13-15.

# **Model Casting Call ‚Äî Skincare Facial Content Shoot (Paid)**

**Date:** Monday, October 13th, 2025
**Time:** 11 AM ‚Äì 4 PM (1-2-hour time slots per model)
**Location:** Studio in Kitsilano *(exact address will be shared with confirmed models)*
**Compensation:** **$100 total for 1-2 hours (plus a complimentary facial)**

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm Brianna, an esthetician creating skincare and facial content for my portfolio. I‚Äôm looking for** 3 models (any gender, 18+)** to take part in a calm facial treatment shoot.

**Shoot details:**
‚ú® Gentle, soothing facial in a relaxing environment üíÜüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
‚ú® Makeup-free, clean skin look
‚ú® Filmed with a** photographer and videographer**
‚ú® Videos/stills used for social media 
‚ú® You‚Äôll receive edited images for your portfolio

‚ú® Glowy skin and compliments from friends will follow ;)

**Requirements:**
‚Ä¢ Comfortable on camera, makeup-free
‚Ä¢ No major skin sensitivities or allergies (we will do a consultation before)
‚Ä¢ Punctual, communicative, and reliable

‚Ä¢ Modelling/acting experience is a plus!

**To apply:**
Please PM me with the following:
‚Ä¢ Your name, a short intro, and your contact information
‚Ä¢ A recent natural photo of your face
‚Ä¢ Confirmation you‚Äôre available on **Monday, Oct 13 (between 11 AM ‚Äì 4 PM)**

‚Ä¢ Optional: if you want to link your socials, send your resume, attach your portfolio or a video, you're more than welcome to, I support creativity :)

This will be a relaxing, paid opportunity ‚Äî perfect for anyone wanting **beauty or skincare portfolio content** in a modern, minimal style üå∏

Kindly note, I will be reaching out to selected talent only. Thank you for your interest and time, and I look forward to reviewing applications!

items.text:
Hello! We are shooting an unpaid improvised short film next week from the 15th to the 18th of October based on the concept for our feature film SOPHIE, and we are looking for an actor for one for the lead roles, to play a charismatic pubcrawl guide (25-35, Male) with a dark side. Shooting will take place on the 15th, 16th, 17th and 18th of October, all night shoots.

If you're interested in knowing more details please send me your showreel or a short introductory video of you and your acting experience, to vasco.cinema.2018@gmail.com.

Sinopsis: On a weekend escape to Copenhagen, Sophie reunites with an old friend and spirals through a night of fleeting connections, as she‚Äôs forced to confront the cost of trying to feel anything at all.

items.text:
ACTORS & CREW & LOCATIONS WANTED ‚Äì NO-BUDGET GRADUATION FILM (English / Multilingual)

I am Nadja, 26, nearing the completion of my acting degree at Cours Florent (Macromedia) in Berlin, and I am looking for ambitious people for **IN FRONT OF** and **BEHIND** the camera.

**Shooting Period:** November 1st ‚Äì November 5th in Berlin

**Budget:** None, however, we have launched a Crowdfunding campaign to create a high-quality short film (max. 15min) that will be submitted to international festivals.

The short film explores a theme that has preoccupied me my entire life: my cultural identity. Am I German? Am I Polish? Can I be both and unite these parts? How much do I owe my parents, who sacrificed so much to enable a better life for me? The film is about four people caught between tradition and their own path, struggling with what the right way forward is. The film will illuminate Polish, Vietnamese, Turkish, and German culture.

**Casting: Roles Still to be Filled (1/2 ‚Äì 1 shooting day per role)**

**Anna's Father (Jerzy)**

Mid-50s ‚Äì Mid-60s; Must speak **Polish**

The Polish immigrant (blue-collar background) who works in a skillful, crafty trade. Driven by the high educational aspirations common among Polish migrants in Germany, he relentlessly pushed Anna toward the *Gymnasium* track and high-status academic success. Must convey **conflicted pride** and strict, yet wounded, authority.

**Linh's Mother (Hoa)**

Mid-50s ‚Äì Mid-60s; Must speak **Vietnamese**

She is **stern and formidable** and places great importance on external appearance and family honor. Her strictness stems from a deep-seated fear that Linh's assimilation will lead to disrespect for the ancestors and personal instability. She **micromanages Linh's appearance**, demanding conservative dress and traditional feminine conduct. 

**Onur's Mother**

Approx. 60; Must speak **Turkish**

Her life‚Äôs priority is the **continuation of the family lineage**, viewing marriage and children as the absolute purpose of life and success. She is completely **oblivious to Onur's true sexuality** and confronts him with a young woman she considers "perfect." Must convey powerful, traditional authority mixed with subtle, genuine softness.

**Onur's Aunt (Leman)**

Approx. 50; Must speak **Turkish**

Onur‚Äôs charismatic and modern aunt, who serves as a vital contrast to the Mother. Leman is wittier, more open, and has a less rigid approach to life in the diaspora. She represents a more assimilated perspective and offers a relaxed energy that provides a potential emotional refuge from family pressure.

**Chris**

Approx. 30 ‚Äì 35; Scene involves **light intimacy** (NO nudity or partial nudity!)

An **athletic, highly attractive businessman** who operates in Anna‚Äôs world of luxury and efficiency. He is polished, charismatic, and carries the effortless confidence of someone who could model formal attire. Initially perceived as a "sex-only" casual date, Chris is actually calm and emotionally perceptive, pushing for a **genuine connection** after six months of casual encounters.

**Crew and Location Search**

We are also looking for comprehensive help on set and in post-production.

**Location Search:**
* We primarily seek a large apartment with an **open-plan kitchen/living area** where we can film the main scene.
* For 1 scene, we are looking for a **Vietnamese restaurant** where we could potentially film for a few hours **BEFORE** the shop opens. No extras or food are needed, just the interior of the restaurant.
* An apartment with a **balcony** where we can film a scene with three people (ideally a *Plattenbau* setting).

If interested, please send an email to: [lostintranslationproduction@gmail.com](mailto:lostintranslationproduction@gmail.com)  or [info@nadja-gallera.de](mailto:info@nadja-gallera.de)

Thank you very much for your attention and help.

Best regards!
